  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Rinse</strong> the rice, add it to a pot with plenty of cold water and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook for 15-20 min or until tender with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> cooked, drain and return to the pot and cover until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, grab a clean plate for the next step</p>\r\n<p><strong>Peel</strong> and finely chop (or grate) the garlic</p>\r\n<p><strong>Combine</strong> the garlic, beef mince, egg, breadcrumbs and 1<span class=\"text-danger\"> (2)</span> soy sauce sachets in a large mixing bowl&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Season</strong> generously with salt and pepper and mix well (use clean hands)&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Divide</strong> the mince mixture into 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">(12)</span> portions</p>\r\n<p><strong>Shape</strong> each portion into a ball (use wet hands for easy shaping)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Transfer</strong> the balls onto your plate and refrigerate until step 6</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Wash</strong>, quarter and shred the cabbage very thinly (discard the woody stem)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Heat</strong> a large, wide-based pan (with a matching lid) over a high heat with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(2 tbsp)</span> vegetable oil</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> hot, add the shredded cabbage and cook on a high heat for 2 min</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> a lid, turn the heat down to medium and cook for a further 4 min or until the cabbage is cooked but retains a slight crunch</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> cooked, remove from the heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the remaining soy sauce, sesame oil and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(2 tbsp)</span> sugar to the cabbage and mix through, then cover and set aside until serving&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-_5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-_5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-_5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-_5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-_5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Heat</strong> a separate pan with 1-2 tbsp vegetable oil on a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>When</strong> hot, add the meatballs and cook on each side for 3 min</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> a lid and cook for a further 5-10 min or until cooked through</p>\r\n<p><strong>Set</strong> the table or do a little washing up while your meatballs are cooking!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-_6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-_6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-_6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-_6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/407.-step-_6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Remove</strong> the lid from the meatball pan and add the hoisin sauce, moving the meatballs around for 30 seconds so that they are evenly coated and glazed</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
